#Text=MH :
#Text=There were a lot of negative reactions from fans when Jaslene won .
#Text=Do you think she was the best choice ?
#Text=If so , why ?
#Text=If not , who would have been the better choice and why ?
#Text=WC : Oh , my God , negative reactions ?
#Text=Are you kidding ?
#Text=Jaslene was , without a doubt , the best model at the time on the show .
#Text=The only possible negative reaction I could think of is that she 's so thin .
#Text=And what people do n't know is that Jaslene could give me a run for my money in eating . [ laughs ]
#Text=She 's just naturally built the way she is .
#Text=MH : Some negative fan reactions were " How could Jaslene sell a product when she ca n't speak English well ?
#Text=She 's not even pretty !
#Text=She looks like a man !
#Text=" Which , I wish I was making it up , but it 's a rather loud fan voice on those points .
#Text=She is from Puerto Rico and represents all that America is — a large nation made up of a multitude of people from different backgrounds and places .
#Text=And Jaslene is beautiful as are we all .
#Text=And yes , I do believe that the fans can be excessively cruel .
#Text=I do n't even consider those folks fans though .
#Text=They 're people who have nothing else better to do with themselves than sit around and bash reality TV contestants on anonymous blog sites .
#Text=MH : You and Diana were some of the only models in this cycle who were working toward a college degree .
#Text=Did you feel that you were smarter than the other girls ?
#Text=Did people at your college watch Top Model to see you and root for you ?
#Text=WC : Smarter ? [ laughs ]
#Text=I do n't like that term because I 'm an honest believer in the fact that people are all relatively smart , just in different things .
#Text=I would say that I was well versed in certain areas that others were not , but that does n't mean I 'm smarter per se .
#Text=And yes , folks at my school definitely watched the show .
#Text=I got really positive feedback !
#Text=They said I represented well .
#Text=Where Whitney is today
#Text=MH : And on that note , a fan wanted to know if you finished your degree at Dartmouth .
#Text=WC : Yes .
#Text=MH : This past May , right ?
#Text=WC : I walked in June .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Do you plan on moving back to Florida , or are you going to continue living in New York City ?
#Text=WC : I 'm definitely going to continue to live in New York for a while .
#Text=I need to be where the industry is .
